=Configure the Keyboard in Ubuntu= 
----

====Follow this guide to assign the Cr-48 media keys to their appropriate functions in Ubuntu 10 (see further down for Ubuntu 11.04 "Natty" setup).==== 
# ====<span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Install Ubuntu by following the guide [[Install Ubuntu|here]]</span>==== 
# ====Install **xbacklight** either by using Synaptic Package Manager or by typing this in the terminal: <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">sudo apt-get install xbacklight</span>==== 
# ====Go to System > Preferences > Keyboard Shortcuts==== 
# ====Click the **Add** button==== 
# ====Under **Name:** type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">Brightness up</span>==== 
# ====Under **Command:** type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">xbacklight -set 100</span>==== 
# ====Click the **Apply** button==== 
# ====Click the **Add** button again==== 
# ====Under **Name:** type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">Brightness down</span>==== 
# ====Under **Command:** type <span style="background-color: #ffff00; font-family: 'Lucida Console',Monaco,monospace;">xbacklight -dec 10</span>==== 
# ====Click the **Apply** button==== 
# ====Scroll down to the bottom of the Keyboard Shortcuts window where you'll find the two shortcuts you just created==== 
# ====Click the right column next to the shortcut **Brightness up** and the words **New shortcut...** will appear==== 
# ====Press the appropriate brightness control button on your Cr-48 keyboard to link that button to the shortcut==== 
# ====Repeat the previous two steps for the **Brightness down** shortcut==== 
# ====Scroll to the top of the Keyboard Shortcuts window and repeat these steps for the volume controls and any other actions you wish to assign to specific keys==== 
# ====It may be necessary to reboot the computer to get everything working==== 


